an><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/9/01 10:13:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> If you're gonna kite w/ a partner, I've found it works best if you do ovals...  Snare MOB, start fluxing the hell out of it, and run the north side of the oval.  Cast when at the east-most point, then kite the south half of the oval, and cast on the west-most point.  all your caster buddies hang out in the middle and chain-nuke to their heart's content.  I've been doing this in RM with cyclopses and an enchanter and a cleric - they both LOVE being able to do damage, and I only use up 20-40m doing this - so I can go pull again while they finish medding. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 31st Season<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usarakentp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>saraken tp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/9/01 10:27:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> Good idea, there. But won't that break aggro, and mobs just attack the middle group? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uskitz01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skitz01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/9/01 10:39:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> I learned to quad with a druid doing wolves in Iceclad.  It took a few runs to get it down, but once we did I found it to be smooth sailing.<br><br>We had the druid snare and round the mobs up (dont have to worry about multiple casts of BoF).  Then I would CoF three times to make sure all aggro was on me and lead the kite using SoTF to gauge range.  The good thing is that CoF and Call of Lightning have very similar cast times - its fun to watch the health bar drop when you hit at the same time.<br><br>The trick is making sure that the two of you run together - especially while you as the wizzy are taking over the aggro.  Make sure the druid follows directly behind you and stops when you stop.<br><br>If you do get aggro split between the two of you, there are two things to do.  You can run a tight braid (i.e. wizzy to the left then cross so wizzy is on right, etc) to get the mobs grouped again.  Simpler but sloppier is to just kite off whatever mobs are on you and then go help your partner.<br><br>Personally, I love to partner with a druid when I can.  Its safer, more social, with less downtime and I dont have to bother with snaring and re-snaring and re-snaring again when BoF gets resisted.  Oh - and when you get good at it, you can kite 6,7, possibly 8 mobs at once, too (most we've done is 6 - but had plenty of mana left over).  I highly recommend it as an alternative to soloing.<br><br> <p>Skitzolious T. F. Elentaari [Fantasy] <br>41st Season Wizard - Vaz Server<br><br>Faeloth Dae`Amarth [Fantasy]<br>Dark Knight of Innorouk's 26th Curse</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dscott12>Dscott12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 6:46:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding with Druid</span><hr size=1> Hi there,<br><br>I've found it to be quite effective quadding with a Druid.  34 and up, so he/she has an AE damage spell.  Especially if one is not lucky enough to have Jboots or potions, the SoW is always there for you.<br><br>I've found, at 35, that quadding with a mixture of Ulthork hunters as well as warriors is quite easily accomplished. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 7:38:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding with Druid</span><hr size=1> not with your flux staff it won't.  You just have to learn to run the oval, and flux EVERYTHING.  Also, if you snare, than light up the targets 2x before your partner opens up, you should be fine, too.  I've been doing this with cyclopses and giant skellies in RM, but no more than 2 so far, while we figure out how to keep everything on me w/out bad adds. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 31st Season<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 10:15:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> this works very well and is a great way to quad mobs that otherwise are not possible to quad solo. If you can kill 2x as fast then its worth it. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></span><p><b><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102 ">Moordian Kilbringer</a></b><br>Warrior of 35 Battle Scars</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rolfe>rolfe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 1:11:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> With a druid partner, she and I were able to do about 20 to 25 dire wolves in one kite yesterday.  Most of you will likely not believe this.  It is a little time consuming.  It took as long as about 2 or 3 quad kites WITHOUT using snare would normally take.  The process is tedious to explain properly.  Email me if you want a detailed explanation in the meantime.  If I get a few emails, I'll probably just post an explanation.  I'm also happy to give a demonstration to any disbelievers.<br><br>Rolfe of Povar<br>rolfewiz@yahoo.com <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rolfe>rolfe</A> at: 11/16/01 11:36:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/16/01 11:46:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> Me and a Druid friend did this a while back.  Basicly whoever was fm first would go pull and we had a set path that we would follow.<br><br>Both casters stay together following the path to each of the way points (whatever handy landmarks you can find).  The person who pulls will nuke about 3 or 4 times before the second person is allowed to join in.  <br><br>Even with that the second person must stay further away from the mobs at all times otherwise you risk splitting agro.<br><br>Sit back down and med, who ever is FM first then pulls again. <p><P></P><P>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=</P><P>Gder of Mithanial Marr</P><P>aka</P><P>Master of his domain</P><P>aka</P><P>gder@gder.net</P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uconfuscius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Confuscius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/18/01 11:31:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.alphalink.com.au/~willie/graphics/face.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> I did well with a monk. Monk pulls, I BoF it, and nuke it straight away. It chases me, monk, bangs on its ass. And repeat. If you agro it enough, it hard hits the monk. Or you can SoTF it. Just another variation to kiting.<br> <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20771" target="_blank">Confuscius</a><br>42nd High Elf Wizard<br>'Great Adventure Partizan'<br>Druzzil Ro</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rolfe>rolfe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/25/01 10:56:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting and partnering with a druid?</span><hr size=1> No one even flinched.  NO ONE is curious as to how to take out 20+ blue mobs in a single kite with only one partner?  I posted a full guide on this method in the AOE grouping section.  If anyone gets use out of it, PLEASE let me know.  It was a lot of work and I'd like to see others get some use out of it.<br><br>Rolfe of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=199.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=199.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=199.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=199.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=199.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=199.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cel